[div class=p 
	"Unfortunately, I have too many optimization concerns about this submission to be able to accept it for publication.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"1) Just in checking the start-up optimization before the very first Toss-Up round, I was able to save 30 frames.  Doing so however changes RNG and yields different puzzles, thus the rest of the run won't sync.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"2) Using the submitted start-up, and checking optimization through both Toss-Up rounds and the first main round.  I was able to save another 30 frames.  Doing so however changes RNG and yields different results in Sheila's spins, and thus desyncs.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"3a) At least some spins are longer than necessary; I'm not sure if you're trying to maximize score, but you can make some spins shorter in order to save time.  If you want to go for a maximum score, then you'll likely need to do a LOT more spinning and letter "guessing" to maximize the prize results.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"3b) You sometimes spin and guess a letter before solving.  This is not necessary and you can solve right away; meaning that 3a above is moot, and there is a ton of free time save available.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"There may be more optimization opportunities as well, but these are enough for me reject this run on the basis of optimization.
	$LF
