[div class=p 
	"Specifically, I'd encourage you to investigate RNG manipulation for this game.  Changing the system time 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=as mentioned by Spikestuff|href=/Forum/Posts/531213)
	", doesn't seem to affect the RNG from my testing.  But, the timing of when inputs occur does affect RNG (i.e. what frame the game is started on and/or when certain start-up options are selected).  Thus, it may be possible to manipulate more favorable actions of the opponents, such as forcing them to lose-a-turn or bankrupt on all their spins.  It may also be possible to manipulate a bonus round solution that doesn't contain any of the RSTLNE letters which would save time of not needing Vanna to uncover them.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Regarding input optimization: use TAStudio in order to ensure that your inputs are occurring on the earliest frame possible to yield the results you desire.  If input delays are necessary in order to manipulate ideal RNG for a faster run, explain those delays in any future submission notes so that a judge won't view them as sloppy/unoptimized play.
	$LF
]div
